CHALLENGE:
Difficulty: "Easy"
Description: "Create a regex that matches valid email addresses (simple version)."
Samples: Match: "user@example.com"; Match: "john.doe@company.co.uk"; Match: "info@site-name.net"; NonMatch: "invalid@"; NonMatch: "@example.com"; NonMatch: "user@.com"
END_CHALLENGE

SOLUTION:
Regex: "^[\w.-]+@[\w.-]+\.[a-zA-Z]{2,}$"
Explanation: "This regex matches an email with username before @, domain name after @, and a TLD of at least 2 letters. [\w.-]+ allows letters, digits, underscores, dots, and hyphens in both username and domain."
END_SOLUTION